<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb9463189-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3" identifier="/us/usc/t39/s203"><num value="203">§ 203.</num><heading> Postmaster General; Deputy Postmaster General</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The chief executive officer of the Postal Service is the Postmaster General appointed under <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s202/c">section 202(c) of this title</ref>. The alternate chief executive officer of the Postal Service is the Deputy Postmaster General appointed under <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s202/d">section 202(d) of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb946318a-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">(<ref href="/us/pl/91/375">Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/721">84 Stat. 721</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb946318b-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idb946318c-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDate" id="idb946318d-2930-11f1-bc69-dbd19d1ebdf3"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section effective <date date="1970-08-12">Aug. 12, 1970</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/91/375/s15/a">section 15(a) of Pub. L. 91–375</ref>, set out as a note preceding <ref href="/us/usc/t39/s101">section 101 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
